##The global multi-country epidemic situation has worsened, the confirmed case sharp increase

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Liu Dong, thepaper.cn

The epidemic of new crown pneumonia is developing rapidly in the world.

This past weekend, the global pandemic has worsened. In East Asia, there has been a 195 per cent increase in confirmed cases in Korea; in southern Europe, there has been a nearly 50-fold increase in cases in Italy; cases are also rising rapidly in Iran and Japan, with many countries reporting their first confirmed cases. These changes could portend a gradual closing of the window of time to contain a global pandemic.

World Health Organization Director-general Strandsee 22 in Geneva with the African Union and the African Center for Disease Control and Prevention officials expressed the concern of the emergency meeting. In his speech, he said the "window of opportunity" to prevent the global spread of the epidemic was narrowing as new cases of pneumonia outside China increased. Currently, Japan, South Korea, Italy and Singapore, the countries with the highest number of reported cases outside China, have all developed community-based infections.

"There are concerns about community transmission in Japan, South Korea, Italy and Iran. We may already be on the brink of a global pandemic. When the virus spreads widely in some countries, it is almost inevitable that it will spread to other countries, because today no one country can completely shut down its connections to the rest of the world. So we expect to experience a pandemic, even if it's not quite there yet, but we're getting there in a disturbing way,"said Anthony Fauci, director of the Institute of Medical Science and a member of the new coronavirus task force, in an interview with the www.thepaper.cn  on Thursday.

Outbreak in South Korea, Italy, Iran rises sharply

Over the weekend, South Korea saw a surge of 398 new cases of pneumonia, a 195 percent increase in just two days, bringing the total nationwide to 602 and the death toll to six. South Korean President Moon jae-in issued an emergency speech on Sunday, announcing an increase in the alert for the new crown disease to its highest level, "serious. ". This would give the government the authority to take more comprehensive measures to contain the outbreak in areas where it is particularly severe. The start of school has been delayed across the country.

In Europe, Italy's Health Ministry announced a sharp rise in new cases for the second day in a row. By the evening of the 23rd, the country's new pneumonia cases had risen from 3 rocket-like cases to 152, including 3 deaths. More worryingly, the health sector has not been able to pinpoint the exact source and route of transmission of the pandemic.

To prevent further spread of the disease, Lombardy and the Veneto region, where the most cases have been reported, have closed more than a dozen municipalities with about 50,000 residents, requiring special permission to enter and leave. In addition, the two regions of the school will be closed for at least a week, museums, cinemas and other places where people gather declared closed. The remaining two days of the ongoing Venice Carnival have also been cancelled. It is worth noting that the Lombardy and Veneto regions are relatively developed regions of the Italian economy, accounting for about 30 per cent of the country's gross domestic product.

In the Middle East, the number of confirmed cases in Iran is also rising rapidly. Iran's Health Ministry confirmed Sunday that the new coronavirus has killed eight people, making it the highest number of reported deaths outside China. To date, 43 cases have been confirmed in Iran. The Iranian government announced that schools, universities and cultural centers in 14 provinces would be closed from Sunday. Iran-related cases have been reported in Lebanon, Iraq and the United Arab Emirates. On the 24th, Turkey and Afghanistan closed their border with Iran because of the epidemic.

America, Africa, sound the alarm

Across the Pacific, the United States is sounding the alarm about the spread of the new crown disease.

Nancy Messonnier, director of the CDC's respiratory disease, said at a weekend telephone briefing, the New York Times reported, the new crown outbreak poses a huge threat to public health and the virus "could become an epidemic" .

As of Friday, at least 34 people in the US had been infected with COVID-19,18 of them returning passengers from the diamond princess. All cases so far have been related to overseas travel.

"We haven't seen a community-based transmission of the new coronavirus in the United States, but it's likely to happen eventually, " Maisonier stressed, "Our goal now remains to slow the spread of the new coronavirus in the United States. This will buy us more time to prepare for the treatment of more cases and to deal with the continued spread of the virus. "

Maisonier also warned that in the coming weeks, if the new coronavirus starts spreading in American communities, health authorities will have to take steps similar to those taken in Asia to prepare for school and business closures.

But who director-general Tan Desai said the agency's biggest concern at the moment is that the new coronavirus could spread in countries with weak health systems. At Saturday's meeting, he warned African leaders of the urgent need to prepare for this. So far, there has been only one confirmed case on the continent and most of the region is free of infection, but health officials have warned that the spread could be deadly in countries where health systems are already strained.
